    {
      "id": "1904750c-f3ba-8050-b3f3-ebca92506a91",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The goal of the work how and why students engaged with different learning resources. Work creates clusters from the interactions of 581 engineering students and, for 44 of them use survey data to understand the motivation behind the usage of those resources. Authors argue that their results may be useful to coach students and design better curricula/resources.",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1904750c-f3ba-8050-b3f3-ebca92506a91",
